# Styling Guide

This project uses [Tailwind CSS](https://tailwindcss.com/) for styling and [shadcn/ui](https://ui.shadcn.com/) for the component library.

## Combining CSS Classes

When you need to conditionally apply CSS classes, use the `cn` utility function from `[src/lib/utils.ts](mdc:src/lib/utils.ts)`. This function is a combination of `clsx` and `tailwind-merge` and helps keep class names clean and readable.

### Example

```tsx
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils"

function MyComponent({ className, isActive }) {
  return (
    <div className={cn("p-4", { "bg-blue-500": isActive }, className)}>
      Hello, world!
    </div>
  )
}
```